text: Saint-Thibaut is a former commune. It is found in the region Hauts-de-France in the Aisne department in the north of France. On 1 January 2022, it was merged into the new commune of Bazoches-et-Saint-Thibaut.Arrêté préfectoral, 30 September 2021 == References == Category:Former communes in Aisne
title: Saint-Thibaut
